The meeting between the Nigerian Labour Congress (NLC) and the House of Representatives Committee on Labour has been postponed due to ongoing negotiation between Labour union and the federal government over national minimum wage. The meeting between the committee and the Union was earlier slated for 2 pm at the National Assembly complex. However, the NLC in a letter informed the committee that the federal government is having a meeting with them at the same time. NLC had issued an ultimatum to the federal government over the delay in the implementation of the new N30, 000 minimum wage. Download Daily Post App.    Subscribe to Daily Post Newsletter.    Advertise with us.   Send us enquiries, press releases.